#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.195"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.195:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.195:0.2"
msgid "20. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "20. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.195:0.3"
msgid "195. Piṅgiyānīsutta "
msgstr "195. Piṅgiyānī "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.195:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.195:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena pañcamattāni licchavisatāni bhagavantaṃ payirupāsanti. "
msgstr "Now at that time around five hundred Licchavis were visiting the Buddha. "

msgctxt "an5.195:1.3"
msgid "Appekacce licchavī nīlā honti nīlavaṇṇā nīlavatthā nīlālaṅkārā, appekacce licchavī pītā honti pītavaṇṇā pītavatthā pītālaṅkārā, appekacce licchavī lohitakā honti lohitakavaṇṇā lohitakavatthā lohitakālaṅkārā, appekacce licchavī odātā honti odātavaṇṇā odātavatthā odātālaṅkārā. "
msgstr "Some of the Licchavis were in blue, of blue color, clad in blue, adorned with blue. And some were similarly colored in yellow, red, or white. "

msgctxt "an5.195:1.4"
msgid "Tyassudaṃ bhagavā atirocati vaṇṇena ceva yasasā ca. "
msgstr "But the Buddha outshone them all in beauty and glory. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.195:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho piṅgiyānī brāhmaṇo uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the brahmin Piṅgīyānī got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said, "

msgctxt "an5.195:2.2"
msgid "“paṭibhāti maṃ, bhagavā, paṭibhāti maṃ, sugatā”ti. "
msgstr "“I feel inspired to speak, Blessed One! I feel inspired to speak, Holy One!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.195:2.3"
msgid "“Paṭibhātu taṃ piṅgiyānī”ti bhagavā avoca. "
msgstr "“Then speak as you feel inspired,” said the Buddha. "

msgctxt "an5.195:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho piṅgiyānī brāhmaṇo bhagavato sammukhā sāruppāya gāthāya abhitthavi: "
msgstr "So the brahmin Piṅgīyānī extolled the Buddha in his presence with a fitting verse. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: Padmaṃ → padumaṃ (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: kokanadaṃ → kokanudaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.195:3.1"
msgid "“Padmaṃ yathā kokanadaṃ sugandhaṃ, "
msgstr "“Like a fragrant pink lotus "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.195:3.2"
msgid "Pāto siyā phullamavītagandhaṃ; "
msgstr "that blooms in the morning, its fragrance unfaded—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.195:3.3"
msgid "Aṅgīrasaṃ passa virocamānaṃ, "
msgstr "see Aṅgīrasa shine, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.195:3.4"
msgid "Tapantamādiccamivantalikkhe”ti. "
msgstr "bright as the sun in the sky!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.240, sc4
msgctxt "an5.195:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho te licchavī pañcahi uttarāsaṅgasatehi piṅgiyāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ acchādesuṃ. "
msgstr "Then those Licchavis clothed Piṅgiyānī with five hundred upper robes. "

msgctxt "an5.195:4.2"
msgid "Atha kho piṅgiyānī brāhmaṇo tehi pañcahi uttarāsaṅgasatehi bhagavantaṃ acchādesi. "
msgstr "And Piṅgiyānī clothed the Buddha with them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an5.195:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā te licchavī etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the Licchavis: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.195:5.2"
msgid "“pañcannaṃ, licchavī, ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Licchavis, the appearance of five treasures is rare in the world. "

msgctxt "an5.195:5.3"
msgid "Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.195:5.4"
msgid "Tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "A Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "an5.195:5.5"
msgid "Tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desetā puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "A person who explains the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One. "

msgctxt "an5.195:5.6"
msgid "Tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "A person who understands the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One. "

msgctxt "an5.195:5.7"
msgid "Tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā dhammānudhammappaṭipanno puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "A person who practices in line with the teaching. "

msgctxt "an5.195:5.8"
msgid "Kataññū katavedī puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "A person who is grateful and thankful. "

msgctxt "an5.195:5.9"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, licchavī, pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "The appearance of these five treasures is rare in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.195:5.10"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
